questions.text: You are working as the Portfolio Manager in the ERP portfolio of Al-Hamd organization. You are currently defining the roles and responsibilities in the portfolio. To define component manager roles and responsibilities, which tools and technique will be used?
questions.explanation:
‘Portfolio Organizational Structural Analysis (POSA)’ is a technique used in ‘Develop Portfolio Management plan’ process to define detailed portfolio roles and responsibilities and to produce the ‘Portfolio Management Organizational Structure (PMOS)’ (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 5.1.2.2, Pg# 61)

- Elicitation Techniques are used to gather and seek information about portfolio. Methods include Coordination, Questionnaire and Surveys, Facilitation
- The other options are the T&T to develop Portfolio Communication Management plan

questions.text: You are the Portfolio Manager of Construction portfolio in Luxury Real Estate and Builders organization. A new regulation has been announced by the government of Pakistan. This regulation will impact your portfolio and compliance is mandatory. Which of the following will most likely be revised as a result of this?
questions.explanation:
Compliance with new regulation may require the postponement of active or planned components, and initiation of new components in the portfolio (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 5.1.3.2, Pg# 63)

- This report is portfolio governance recommendations based on portfolio performance, component proposals, and risks as well as capability and capacity of resources, funding allocations, and future investment requirements.
- The situation does not mention of an issue situation. Portfolio issue Register does not need to be updated here
- Portfolio Management plan has 'Manage Compliance' section that documents how the Portfolio Manager will address compliance requirements. It may also need to be updated. However, 'Portfolio' is a better choice in this scenario

questions.text: Portfolio Management is the coordinated management of one or more portfolios to achieve strategic objectives. The portfolio management processes ensure:

options.text: Monitoring strategic changes and optimization of organizational resources
Measuring the degree by which program satisfy organizational needs

questions.explanation:
Management of strategic changes and optimization and balancing of component and organizational resources are few of the activities of portfolio management (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 5,6)

- The other choices represent project and program management

questions.text: You are performing risk management as the Portfolio Manager of Social Development portfolio in Sindh province. How will you report major risks to key stakeholders?

options.text: During meetings with the portfolio governance board

questions.explanation:
The best way to communicate major portfolio risk information to key stakeholders is via Portfolio Risk Reports. Had the question asked about communicating all portfolio wide risks with information to key/specific portfolio stakeholders then Portfolio Risk Register would have been the better choice

- Scenario is asking about reporting of major/key risks to key stakeholders. RR records all the risks that stakeholders may not be interested in, so the better choice here is reporting via Portfolio Risk reports
- Major risks may be presented to key stakeholders during phase gate reviews with PGB, but they will be reported via Portfolio Reports
- Risk reporting will happen via RR or via Portfolio Risk reports, not via Issue Register

questions.text: Which among the following is the role and responsibility of Portfolio Governance board in your organization?

options.text: Engages stakeholders in projects and programs

questions.explanation:
Portfolio Governance body is made up of one or more individuals that ensures decision making, alignment of portfolio components to organizational strategic objectives, component authorization and portfolio oversight (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Pg# 19)

- 'Provide resources' is the role and responsibility of Portfolio Sponsor
- 'Engages stakeholders in projects and programs' is the role and responsibility of component managers (Project and Program Management)
- 'Guiding the selection of components' is the role and responsibility of Portfolio Manager

questions.text: The Chairperson of your portfolio governance board has complained to you that the monthly portfolio performance reports received by her contains redundant, inconsistent and inaccurate information. Which portfolio management process and the T&T is involved here?

options.text: Develop Communication Management Plan, Communication Requirement Analysis
Develop Communication Management Plan, Stakeholder Analysis
Manage Portfolio Information, Communication Requirement Analysis

questions.explanation: ‘Communication Req Analysis’ technique will be reviewed in this case during the ‘Manage Portfolio Information’ process to check if meaningful info has been extracted from raw communication data to present to key SHs such as Chairperson (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, Section 7.2.2.3, Pg# 117)

questions.text: Mr. Nasir is the Portfolio Manager for EBA Incorporation. He is executing the Quality Assurance portfolio of the organization, and working to ensure that the component reports received are aggregated into a more meaningful and accurate information to present to portfolio stakeholders. Which tool and technique has he used for this?
questions.explanation:
Communication Req Analysis will be reviewed in this case during the ‘Manage Portfolio Information’ process to check if meaningful and accurate info has been extracted from raw communication data to present to key SHs. Hint: One way to help make data meaningful is to build forecasts based on trends in the data

- Communication Methods include visual representations of the data and information receive such as dashboards, resource histograms, and a communication calendar
- Stakeholder Analysis identifies the stakeholders, determine the different individuals and groups, and determine their concerns, interests, and influence.
- PMIS provide technology-based or manual methods of capturing and managing all portfolio-related communication needs. For communication and information management specifically, the PMIS can store information, summarize it for reporting, and assist in managing communication channels.

questions.text:
Your portfolio belongs to Motive Safety Inc. has 3 components namely:
1. AI Camera upgrade project
2. Self-driven vehicles research project
3. Taiwan Mandate
In which of the below categories will you assign the ‘Self-driven vehicles research project ‘?
questions.explanation:
‘Self-driven vehicles research project’ is more suitable for Foundational (Research) category (Reference: Standard of Portfolio Management 3rd ed, section 5.2.2.2, Pg# 68)

Once identified, the list of existing and proposed portfolio components needs to be organized into relevant organization groups to which a common set of decision filters and criteria may be applied for evaluation, selection, and prioritization. The portfolio components in a given group have a common goal and are measured on the same basis regardless of their origin in the organization.

Hint: For exam, know the Portfolio Component Categorization criteria from Standard of Portfolio Mgmt, 3rd ed

- AI camera upgrade project belongs to Process improvement category
- Taiwan Mandate project belongs to Regulatory / Compliance category
